<dl id="n11024a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11024a">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11024a"> 24(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> swore everything he / swore was untrue <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n11024a"><li>FW 520.28 </li><li><a href="../../flex/rA/lexrA.htm#n11024a">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/rA/l39rA.htm#n11024a">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n11024a">MS BL 47482b-86</ms> </li><li>JJA 58:047 <a name="rA2d" href="../../ff/fdra/rda.htm#rA2d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/r/ra2d.htm#n11024a">Draft: III&sect;3A.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Outrageous Act / Stationmaster&apos;s House Fired Into. / Youth of 16 and His Oath.</b> At Galway District Court, before Mr. Sean Ford, Edward Connelly and John Keller were charged with firing into the residence of Mr. J. Bristley, stationmaster, Moycullen, smashing the windows and otherwise damaging the house. ... &ldquo;Do you remember the statement you made and that you were on your oath?&rdquo; asked the justice, and the witness replied &ldquo;It was all lies,&rdquo; at which there was some laughter in which the witness joined. / The justice remonstrated with the witness, reminding him that he was in a court of justice and not a concert room. He said it was a disgraceful thing that a youth of sixteen should take an oath and then <mark>swear that everything that he had sworn was untrue</mark>. <small> <a name="CT24may24" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CT24may24"><cite title="source">Connacht Tribune</cite></a> (24 May 1924) 5/2</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
